Episodes.Title: Little Green Men
Episodes.Plot: With the X-Files closed, Scully has been assigned as an instructor at the FBI Academy while Mulder is doing menial surveillance work. After meeting with Senator Matheson, one of his supporters in regards to the X-Files, Mulder disobeys orders and heads to an abandoned SETI site in Puerto Rico which has inexplicably reactivated itself and could provide proof of contact with extra-terrestrial life.
Episodes.GuestStars: Vanessa Morley, Marcus Turner, Les Carlson, Fulvio Cecere, Deryl Hayes, Dwight McFee, Gary Hetherington, Bob Wilde, Mike Gomez, Raymond J. Barry, Lisa Ann Beley

Episodes.Title: The Host
Episodes.Plot: A.D. Skinner sends Mulder to investigate a body which washed into the New Jersey sewer from the ocean. Mulder believes that the basic blue-collar assignment is punishment, but by Skinner's own admission, what he discovers is a true X-File.
Episodes.GuestStars: Marc Baur, Matthew Bennett, Freddy Andreiuci, Don MacKay, Hrothgar Mathews, Gabrielle Rose, Ron Suave, Dmitri Boudrine, Raoul Ganeev, William MacDonald, Darin Morgan, Steven Williams

Episodes.Title: Blood
Episodes.Plot: When several violent deaths in a small farming community are connected by the destruction of digital devices, Mulder believes that people are being driven to kill by the use of subliminal messages in the digital readouts.
Episodes.GuestStars: William Sanderson, John Cygan, Kimberly Patton, George Touliatos, John Harris, Gerry Rousseau, William Mackenzie, Diana Stevan, David Fredericks, Kathleen Duborg, B.J. Harrison, Andre Daniels

Episodes.Title: Sleepless
Episodes.Plot: Mulder reluctantly accepts a new partner, Agent Alex Krycek, and they investigate the deaths of several Green Beret soldiers who participated in a sleep deprivation experiment during the Vietnam war.
Episodes.GuestStars: Mitchell Kosterman, Don Thompson, David Adams, Michael Puttonen, Anna Hagan, Paul Bittante, Claude de Martino, Nicholas Lea, Jon Gries, Tony Todd

Episodes.Title: Duane Barry (1)
Episodes.Plot: Mulder is called to a hostage situation involving Duane Barry, a former FBI Agent who claims to be an alien abductee and wants to get back to the abduction site with someone who will be taken instead of him. Unfortunately, the someone he eventually chooses is Scully.
Episodes.GuestStars: Steve Railsback, Nicholas Lea, Frank C. Turner, Fred Henderson, Stephen E. Miller, Barbara Pollard, Sarah Strange, Robert Lewis, Tosca Baggoo, Tim Dixon, Prince Maryland, John Sampson, Michael Dobson, CCH Pounder

Episodes.Title: Ascension (2)
Episodes.Plot: When Mulder finds out that Scully was kidnapped by Duane Barry, he risks the wrath of his superiors and the annoyance of Agent Krycek in order to do whatever it takes to find her. Meanwhile, Krycek is found to be reporting Mulder's activities to the Cigarette-Smoking Man.
Episodes.GuestStars: Steve Railsback, Meredith Bain Woodward, Peter LaCroix, Steve Makaj, Peter Lapres, Bobby L. Stewart, Nicholas Lea

Episodes.Plot: Mulder, back on the X-Files but alone for the first time, investigates a series of vampire-like murders in Los Angeles and finds himself falling for the one woman that may be the prime suspect.
Episodes.Writer: Chris Ruppenthal, Glen Morgan, James Wong
Episodes.GuestStars: Frank Ferrucci, Tom McBeath, Gustavo Moreno, Justina Vail, Malcolm Stewart, Ken Kramer, Roger Allford, Richard Yee, John Tierney, David Livingstone, Guyle Frazier, Perrey Reeves, Frank Military, Brad Loree

Episodes.Title: One Breath
Episodes.Plot: Scully mysteriously appears in a Washington hospital, alive but in a coma, and Mulder must fight to keep her alive in order to find out what happened to her and who did it to her. Meanwhile, Scully fights her own personal battle as she decides whether to stay or go on to the next world.
Episodes.GuestStars: Melinda McGraw, Jay Brazeau, Nicola Cavendish, Lorena Gale, Ryan Michael, Tegan Moss, Don S. Davis

Episodes.Title: Firewalker
Episodes.Plot: Mulder and Scully, reunited at last, head for an active volcano under a geological study and find a deadly life form that can survive in the searing heat of the crater and is killing the scientists to avoid being discovered.
Episodes.GuestStars: Bradley Whitford, Tuck Milligan, Leland Orser, Shawnee Smith, Hiro Kanagawa, Torren Rolfsen, David Kaye

Episodes.Title: Red Museum
Episodes.Plot: While investigating the connection between the abduction of several teenagers and a rural religious cult, Mulder and Scully discover a secret test being performed on the children using the "Purity Control" alien DNA from 'The Erlenmeyer Flask' which leads Mulder to "the crew-cut man", Deep Throat's murderer.
Episodes.GuestStars: Gillian Barber, Bob Frazer, Robert Clothier, Elisabeth Rosen, Cameron Labine, Tony Sampson, Crystal Verge, Gerry Nairn, Brian McGugan, Paul Sand, Steve Eastin, Mark Rolston, Lindsey Ginter

Episodes.Title: Excelsis Dei
Episodes.Plot: Mulder and Scully uncover strange occurrences in an elderly care home when one of the nurses is attacked by an unseen force she claims to be one of the 90 year old residents.
Episodes.GuestStars: Frances Bay, Teryl Rothery, Eric Christmas, David Fresco, Sab Shimono, Tasha Simms, Sheila Moore, Jerry Wasserman, Jon Cuthbert, Paul Jarrett, Ernie Prentice

Episodes.Title: Aubrey
Episodes.Plot: When a detective mysteriously uncovers the remains of an FBI agent who disappeared in the 1940s while investigating a similar murder case to one she is now on, Mulder and Scully believe that the original killer had passed his genetic trait of violence to his grandchild.
Episodes.GuestStars: Deborah Strang, Morgan Woodward, Terry O'Quinn, Joy Coghill, Robyn Driscoll, Peter Flemming, Sarah Jane Redmond, Emanuel Hajek

Episodes.Title: Irresistible
Episodes.Plot: A mortuary worker who gets his thrills from collecting hair and fingernails from the dead begins killing his soon-to-be collectibles himself and sets his seriously disturbed sights on Scully.
Episodes.GuestStars: Nick Chinlund, Robert Thurston, Bruce Weitz, Christine Willes, Deanna Milligan, Glynis Davies, Tim Progosh, Dwight McFee, Maggie O'Hara, Mark Saunders, Clara Hunter, Denalda Williams, Kathleen Duborg

Episodes.Title: Die Hand Die Verletzt
Episodes.Plot: The ritualistic murder of a teenager in a small town gets Mulder and Scully caught up in a secret occult practice within the local school's PTA and a substitute teacher with strange powers.
Episodes.GuestStars: Susan Blommaert, Dan Butler, Heather McComb, P. Lynn Johnson, Shaun Johnson, Travis MacDonald, Michele Goodger, Larry Musser, Frank Czinege, Laura Harris, Doug Abrahams

Episodes.Title: Fresh Bones
Episodes.Plot: While investigating several deaths and murders within a Haitian refugee camp, Mulder and Scully get caught in the middle of a secret war between the camp commander and a Voodoo priest.
Episodes.GuestStars: Kevin Conway, Katya Gardener, Roger R. Cross, Peter Kelamis, Adrien Malebranche, Bruce A. Young, Daniel Benzali, Jamil Walker Smith, Callum Keith Rennie, Matt Hill

Episodes.Title: Colony (1)
Episodes.Plot: After the obituaries of four identical men are e-mailed to Mulder, the agents are contacted by a shadowy CIA agent who tells them about a bounty hunter sent to wipe out the beginning of a colony of clones. Meanwhile Mulder is distracted by the sudden reappearance of his sister Samantha.
Episodes.GuestStars: Brian Thompson, David L. Gordon, Andrew Johnston, Tim Henry, Michael McDonald, Capper McIntyre, Bonnie Hay, James Leard, Linden Banks, Kim Restell, Richard Sargent, Ken Roberts, Michael Rogers, Oliver Becker, Dana

Episodes.Title: End Game (2)
Episodes.Plot: The alien bounty hunter kidnaps Scully and wants to trade her for Mulder's sister, who is revealed to be a clone herself. After the trade goes badly and Mulder discovers the truth about Samantha, he tracks the bounty hunter to his ship buried in the arctic ice and demands the whereabouts of his real sister.
Episodes.GuestStars: Brian Thompson, Garry Davey, Andrew Johnston, Allan Lysell, J. B. Bivens, Oliver Becker, Beatrice Zeilinger, Bonnie Hay, Megan Leitch, Colin Cunningham

Episodes.Title: Fearful Symmetry
Episodes.Plot: Mulder and Scully investigate strange attacks from invisible animals inside a zoo which is near a known UFO hot spot.
Episodes.GuestStars: Jayne Atkinson, Lance Guest, Jack Rader, Charles André, Garvin Cross, Tom Glass, Jody St. Michael, Lenno Britos

Episodes.Title: Død Kalm
Episodes.Plot: When half the crew of a Navy ship abandon their boat in a life raft and are rescued 18 hours later looking about 60 years older than they should be, Mulder suggests that the ship is caught in a time field which is speeding up their aging.
Episodes.GuestStars: John Savage, Mar Anderson, Vladimir Kulich, David Cubitt, Dmitry Chepovetsky, Claire Riley, Stephen Dimopoulos, John McConnach, Robert Metcalfe, Kelly Irving

Episodes.Title: Humbug
Episodes.Plot: Mulder and Scully travel to Gibsonton, Florida, a town built and populated by circus and sideshow performers to investigate the death of Jerald Glazebrook, The Alligator Man. While searching for leads on the killer, the agents come across many bizarre characters including the local sheriff who was once known as Jim Jim, the Dog-Faced Boy.
Episodes.GuestStars: Jim Rose, Wayne Grace, George Tipple, Alex Diakun, John Payne, Alvin Law, Blair Slater, Devin Walker, Debis Simpson, Michael J. Anderson, The Enigma, Vincent Schiavelli

Episodes.Title: The Calusari
Episodes.Plot: The suspicious circumstances of a toddler's death leads Mulder and Scully into a Romanian exorcism ritual involving a young boy possessed by his stillborn twin.
Episodes.GuestStars: Helene Clarkson, Joel Palmer, Lilyan Chauvin, Ric Reid, Bill Dow, Oliver Wildsmith, Jeremy Issac Wildsmith, Christine Willes, Kay E. Kuter, Jacqueline Danieneau, Bill Croft, George Josef, Campbell Lane

Episodes.Title: F. Emasculata
Episodes.Plot: When a plague-like illness kills ten men inside a maximum security prison, Scully tries to get into the quarantine site and discover the cause and origin of the contagion, while Mulder and a group of US Marshals track two escapees who may be infected.
Episodes.GuestStars: Charles Martin Smith, Dean Norris, John Pyper-Ferguson, John Tench, Morris Panych, Lynda Boyd, Alvin Sanders, Kim Kondrashoff, Chilton Crane, Bill Rowat, Jude Zachary, Angelo Vacco, Jenny-Lynn Hutcheson

Episodes.Title: Soft Light
Episodes.Plot: An experiment in dark matter accidentally turns a scientist's shadow into a deadly weapon that can unzip a person's molecules if they are touched by it.
Episodes.GuestStars: Tony Shalhoub, Kevin McNulty, Kate Twa, Nathaniel Deveaux, Robert Rozen, Donna Yamamoto, Forbes Angus, Guyle Frazier, Steve Bacic, Craig Brunanski

Episodes.Title: Our Town
Episodes.Plot: After several disappearances in a small town, Mulder and Scully investigate and find hundreds of human bones in the river. They discover that the man behind the town's main source of wealth, a chicken processing plant, has found a way to prolong his life through cannibalism.
Episodes.GuestStars: Gary Grubbs, John Milford, Caroline Kava, Robin Mossley, Timothy Webber, Hrothgar Mathews, Gabrielle Miller, John MacLaren, Robert Moloney, Carrie Cain Sparks

Episodes.Title: Anasazi (1)
Episodes.Plot: When Mulder obtains what could be the original and uncut MJ documents containing information about the government's knowledge of extraterrestrial life; his shadowy enemies step up their harassment of him, eventually leading to his apparent murder.
Episodes.GuestStars: Chris Carter, Bernie Coulson, Aurelio Dinunzio, Paul McLean, Byron Chief-Moon, Renae Morriseau, Ken Camroux, Mitchell Davies, Dakota House
